---

## What This Index Measures

The SPI evaluates 171 countries across 57 indicators organized into three 
dimensions: Basic Human Needs, Foundations of Wellbeing, and Opportunity. 
Critically, it deliberately excludes economic indicators like GDP — making 
it one of the only global indexes that measures social outcomes directly 
rather than as a proxy of wealth. This makes it particularly useful for 
detecting the gap between economic growth and genuine human flourishing.

