## Notes & Caveats

- The SPI does not currently include measures of subjective wellbeing or 
  life satisfaction by design — use the World Happiness Report as a 
  complement for that dimension.
- Wealth concentration in the top 1%, judicial efficiency, and 
  transportation infrastructure are not captured — known gaps acknowledged 
  by the publishers.
- Premium access is required for full country profiles and downloadable 
  datasets. Summary data and rankings are freely available.
- The index is now branded as the "AlTi Global Social Progress Index" 
  following a partnership with AlTi Global, though the methodology and 
  publisher remain the same.

